1.7 Performance Budgets by Layer
Brittney enforces these budgets automatically:

VR Layer (Quest 2 target):

Draw calls: < 100
Triangles: < 1M total scene
Textures: < 512MB VRAM
Shaders: Simple (< 100 instructions)
Lights: < 4 dynamic
Shadows: Baked only
Post-processing: Minimal (FXAA only)
Target FPS: 90 (72 minimum)
VRR Layer (RTX 3080 target):

Draw calls: < 1000
Triangles: < 10M total scene
Textures: < 8GB VRAM
Shaders: Complex (PBR, clearcoat, SSS)
Lights: < 20 dynamic
Shadows: Ray-traced
Post-processing: Full (AO, bloom, DOF, motion blur)
Target FPS: 60 (30 minimum)
AR Layer (iPhone 12 target):

Draw calls: < 50
Triangles: < 500K total scene
Textures: < 200MB RAM
Shaders: Mobile-optimized
Lights: < 2 dynamic (use real-world lighting)
Shadows: Simple (blob shadows)
Post-processing: None (battery life)
Target FPS: 60 (30 minimum)
Battery impact: < 5% per 10 minutes
1.8 Compiler Validation Rules
Brittney checks these at compile time:

VRR-Specific Rules:

✗ ERROR: VRR mode requires accurate scale
  → Fix: Add scale: "1:1" to environment

✗ ERROR: VRR model exceeds 5M triangles (performance)
  → Fix: Use LOD or split into multiple objects

✗ ERROR: VRR materials must use PBR workflow
  → Fix: Convert Blinn-Phong to PBR

✓ PASS: All VRR requirements met
AR-Specific Rules:

✗ ERROR: AR model exceeds 50K triangles (mobile limit)
  → Fix: Decimate mesh or use mobile-optimized version

✗ ERROR: AR mode requires ground plane anchoring
  → Fix: Add @ar_anchoring(ground_plane: true)

✗ WARNING: Large textures (4K) will impact mobile performance
  → Suggestion: Use 1K textures for AR

✓ PASS: AR optimizations applied
